{
  "stem": "11472.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He had two acres of garden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "For a Jewish family, this was very unusual.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But he loved trees, he loved-- anyway, he [SIGHS] loved to grow things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He covered them up, and he covered up my uncle Velvel had also in the barn in a bunker, covered them all up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And he evidently camouflaged a bunker for himself, near the well, because in the middle of the garden, they had a big well.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Evidently, the gardener next door gave them all away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He wanted to make sure that he would possess the house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Because there were two houses adjoining with garden.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And he gave them away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They came down-- somebody came and they said to me, not to me, to my mother, that my grandfather, my great grandfather was laying by the well.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They shot him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Evidently, he didn't want to leave and they shot him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was my father's family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The whole Dodek family disappeared in one day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody disappeared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All my aunts, my uncle, my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father was away trying to help other people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When he came back, oh, how he cried, oh, how he cried for his parents, [SOBBING] for his sister and brothers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[CRYING] He was sitting around.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He couldn't believe himself.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were like in shock-- we didn't know what to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And to lose a family, everyone is erased in one day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Everybody disappeared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Their clothing were there, their food were there, but they weren't there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A week later, the Gestapo came to the Judenrat, and they said our town is becoming judenfrei-- that means free of Jews.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We have to move to Borszczow to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Well, my grandmother and my parents said no, we're not going to the ghetto to Borszczow, since the men were free.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
